  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nAnvil\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (20b2926 2022-06-10T00:15:22.550741Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nanvil\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nI'm trying to bypass [this check](https://github.com/bluealloy/revm/blob/5e1c319ac06db1124259a2a1b54f69cabd039541/crates/revm/src/evm_impl.rs#L82-L87) in fork mode. I tried both \"\" and \"0x\" for code value, trying to set a contract's code to nothing to use it like an EOA. This trick is used in [ape-safe](https://safe.ape.tax) which I'm planning to port to ape+foundry. The problem is only present in fork mode.\r\n\r\nshell commands\r\n```bash\r\nanvil -p 7545 --fork-url http://127.0.0.1:8545\r\nhttp post :7545 jsonrpc=2.0 id=1 method=anvil_setCode params:='[\"0xFEB4acf3df3cDEA7399794D0869ef76A6EfAff52\", \"0x\"]'\r\nhttp post :7545 jsonrpc=2.0 id=1 method=eth_getCode params:='[\"0xFEB4acf3df3cDEA7399794D0869ef76A6EfAff52\", \"latest\"]'\r\n```\r\n\r\nanvil output\r\n```\r\nListening on 127.0.0.1:7545\r\nanvil_setCode\r\neth_getCode\r\nthread 'tokio-runtime-worker' panicked at 'Should not be called. Code is already loaded.', evm/src/executor/fork/backend.rs:498:9\r\nnote: run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` environment variable to display a backtrace\r\nfish: Job 1, 'anvil -p 7545 --fork-url http:/â€¦' terminated by signal SIGABRT (Abort)\r\n```",
